    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Mobile</placeName>
                <date>Febry 7th 1857</date>
            </p>
            <p>My Dear Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your letter of the<lb/>
                <date>30th</date> reached me only today &amp; too<lb/> late for reply by return
                mail<lb/> &amp; I have been so much engaged<lb/> through the day that this is
                the<lb/> first moment I could devote<lb/> to you. As it is 10 P. M. I shall<lb/>
                write but a few lines &amp; get<lb/> it off if possible by the morning<lb/>
                mail.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I need not say to you<lb/> how deeply <persName>M</persName> &amp; I
                were pained<lb/> to hear of your misfortune<lb/> you must be aware that<lb/> we feel
                it as sensibly as if it<lb/> were our own—more so in<lb/> fact, as we have never
                met<lb/> with a serious loss like this<lb/> &amp; could bear it better perhaps<lb/>
                than you can in your present<lb/> state of health.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I must scold<lb/> you a little now however—</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>you know that I am at your<lb/> service as far as I have the<lb/> power &amp; yet you
                give me<lb/> no particulars, or anything to<lb/> form a guess even about your<lb/>
                obligations or wants—this is<lb/> not right &amp; you know it. It<lb/> is not what I
                would have done<lb/> to you, were our positions reversed<lb/> &amp; therefore as
                soon as you get<lb/> this sit down &amp; give me the<lb/> figures &amp; let me see
                if I can<lb/> do anything to assist you.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I shall remit you by <date>Tuesdays</date><lb/> mail $500—to help
                you through<lb/> with any immediate payments<lb/> you may have to
                make—<add>?</add><lb/> I hope to hear either through<lb/> yourself or
                        <persName>Nell<add>?</add></persName> something more<lb/> of your
                affairs.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My eyes are very<lb/> much fatigued tonight &amp; I must<lb/> close
                this now. Our nurse very<lb/> foolishly mistook the moonlight last<lb/> night for
                daylight &amp; woke us all up</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>at 3 A. M. since when I have<lb/> not had a wink of sleep &amp; my eyes<lb/> are dim
                in consequence.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The children &amp; <persName>M</persName> are well<lb/> so am
                    I—<persName>Dew</persName> the best the<lb/> worst, the most provoking &amp;
                the<lb/> dearest little creature in the<lb/> world—E<add>?</add> not to be
                    <add>?</add>d<lb/> anywhere.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Hoping to hear from<lb/> you again shortly &amp; with<lb/>
                assurances of our deep regret<lb/> at the loss you have sustained<lb/> we remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Yr sincere friends</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">M &amp; S Wolff</persName>
            </p>
            <p>I did not get my letter off after<lb/> all &amp; consequently enclose you<lb/> check
                for $500 this morning.<lb/> will send you more as soon<lb/> as I know your wants.<lb/>
                <sic>Dont</sic> be disheartened at my<lb/> rate.</p>
        </body>
